With his keen
interest in the telephone industry and engineering, Blomeyer was also a prolific writer contributing articles to several publications including: The Magazine of Business; Telephony: The American Telephone Journal; Business, A Magazine for Office Store, and Factory; Public Utilities Fortnightly;
American Telephone Journal, and Popular Mechanics. He was also known throughout the telephone industry as the author of a series of booklets entitled: Letters to Managers. By 1934, copies of the ten book series numbered over three million in circulation.
